title: Rosa Kafaji
text:
Rusul Rosa Kafaji (born 5 July 2003) is a Swedish <a href="Association%20football">football</a> striker who plays for <a href="AIK%20Fotboll%20%28women%29">AIK</a> in the Swedish <a href="Damallsvenskan">Damallsvenskan</a>.
Early life.
Kajafi was born to parents who are originally from <a href="Iraq">Iraq</a> and her father moved back there after her parents' divorce.
Club career.
Kafaji grew up in <a href="Akalla">Akalla</a> and started playing football in Kallhälls FF when she was eight years old. After that, Kafaji played for Bele Barkarby FF before she went to <a href="AIK%20Fotboll%20%28women%29">AIK</a> before the 2015 season. Kafaji made her debut for the A-team in the <a href="Elitettan">Elitettan</a> in 2019 and scored four goals and three assists in seven matches during the season. In the <a href="2020%20Elitettan">2020 season</a>, she scored 12 goals in 18 matches and helped AIK to be promoted to the Damallsvenskan.
International career.
In February 2021, Kafaji was selected for the <a href="Sweden%20women%27s%20national%20football%20team">Swedish women's national team</a> for the first time.
